records.addlTxt:
Zoom appearances. 
Defendant in custody at Manitowoc County Jail.
The State moves to delete the repeater enhancers on counts 2 and 5.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 2, possess methamphetamine. Convicted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 5, resist/obstruct officer. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1, 3 and 4.  Motion granted.
On count 2, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1)	Pay court costs;
2)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3)	provide DNA sample;
4)	assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5)	any other counseling, treatment, assessments as recommended by the agent;
6)	maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
7)	maintain absolute sobriety, except for prescribed medications; taken in prescribed doses;
8)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.

On count 5, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for thirty (30) days, time served.
The defendant has credit for 34 days.
$280.00 court costs imposed, to be paid as a condition of probation on count 2.
Minutes.
